reviews.review_text: In the shadow of the moon... Another great show from early '78. The January shows are particularly good and they lead up to the great performances of 2/3 and 2/5 of that year. A bright and focused sound throughout, especially during Terrapin Station. I wouldn't go without any show from Jan. '78.
1-31-78 Exellent both in performance and sound quality. Thanks Charlie.

Uptown Superb Scarlet>Fire! Great show all around.
January '78 was a good month!
2nd set lights the fire phils up in the mix, love donna shows they make the S>F transfer buttery smooth

This show is HOTT!!!! Crystal clear sound. Superb playin'.
Highlights for this head are:
Tenn Jed
TLEO
Scar-Fire
Terrapin
...Enjoy....

Better Than Expected This show was surprisingly good (I don't particularly like 1978 as a whole), and a lot of the songs that sounded best to me are not songs that I'm terribly interested in hearing all of the time.  

For instance, Minglewood really smoked, and Keith sounded interested in playing.  Ditto for They Love Each Other.  The Scarlet/Fire (which is a typical favorite), while not the best ever, was high-quality throughout.  Even Good Lovin at the end was fun to listen to.

I'd recommend this show if you aren't looking for a way out-there vibe, but just some good songs well played.
Philin it up! This is a wonderful representation of the Greatful Dead. You can hear the patience that can only come from playing night after night to an auidience of one.

First show ever I just started to listen to the GD channel on XM and heard about this site... instantly, I wanted to hear the first show I ever went to... it was this 1/31/78 show at the uptown.   great memories and a great show!
Unbelievable. Easily one of my 10 favorite shows.

Incredible Sound Q Worth the stars just for that. (To be super picky there is some diginoise during LIG.)

They Love Each Other through Playing In The Band is very good GD.

Scarlet Begonias If this is in your top ten you degrade all your reviews from previous years. There are ten better shows from each year between 1968-1974 at the very least and more like 50 from 1972, for example.

However, this is a decent show from a year that had potential. Between Minglewood and Terrapin I was neither bored nor thrilled.
Yes, show is...and The Candyman Patch doesnt have Johnson speaking Whatever, top ten, this show is so good its bad.

Shall we call it by a name... Reviews all over the place on this show?

Uptown Winter '78 Run- Night 2 Folkhippy's got a point: This winter tour is hot. Of course, much of it is marred by Jerry's laryngitis at the start and the consequent vocal issues in recovery. But raspy-Jer' can still play his guitar and he certainly gets five-stars for trying. I'd amend his comment, though: some of the early Jan. shows aren't great. Tour really lifts off from Eugene on the 22nd to the end, Cedar Falls on 5 Feb. 

I'm partial to the third night of the run (and the excellent SBD recently uploaded), but this night rivals it and might even be its best. My first set highlights include a strong Half-Step opener, a drippy They Love Each Other, and a smoking Let it Grow to close. Second set, though, is where it's at. The boys came to play. This scarlet-fire is better than previous Chicago one on 13 May '77. Samson is a rager, and then we're treated to a nearly 60-minute suite that includes Terrapin->PITB->drums/space->Black Peter->Truckin'->Good Lovin'. So good, there's no encore!
Really Hot and Smoking More great January shows from the 22nd and following

Get on the Bus ! Really strong playing from the boys on this one!
and super vocals from Donna and Bobby to help get us over Jerry's bout with laryngitis.
Many great reviews below to showcase the song highlights. IMHO, an excellent Passenger deserves a shoutout too !!!
